<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1793,1962]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Male 
<quantity box="[219,357,1793,1818]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.05" metricValueMax="7.4" metricValueMin="6.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="7.05" valueMax="7.4" valueMin="6.7">6.7–7.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[434,573,1794,1818]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.9">2.9–3.1 mm</quantity>
across humeral angles. Color dull stramineous; vertex with pair of brown maculae dorsomesad of ocelli; pronotum, scutellum and forewing with numerous small black spots, some on forewing merging to form larger spots; exposed part of mesonotum with pair of submedial transverse black lines (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1901,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,193,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,193,1657]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dorsal and lateral habitus. A, B, Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov.; C, D, Decliviassus maculatus sp. nov.; E, F, Decliviassus nudus sp. nov.; G, H, Kanchanaburiassus maculatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253712/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,227,1902,1926]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D). 
<collectingCountry box="[303,359,1901,1926]" name="India" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia setal rows PD, AD, and AV with 19, 12, and 
<number box="[932,960,1902,1926]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="14.0">14</number>
macrosetae respectively; tarsomere I with 
<number box="[151,165,1937,1962]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="6.0">6</number>
platellae.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253719/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" targetBox="[190,1399,205,1542]" targetPageId="16">
